args:
Cleo's attitude toward the prince has been
muddled since speaking with Tartarus, so she
heads off alone to a hollow of the tree as her
companions rest. Lost in the midst of a deep
mana fog, a figure suddenly appears—none
other than the Alberius of the past!
I shall see her safe! Haaaaah!
Thank you, Elisanne. I thought we'd slain\nthem all and foolishly let my guard slip.
Call it recompense for the countless\nnumber of scrapes, bruises, and breaks\nyou have healed for me.
Yes, of course. I'm sorry for worrying you.
We've been beset by new and unfamiliar\nfoes for some time now, but must be ever\nat the ready for more.
Every time a new fiend shows up, my heart\nstarts doing the whole kick drum thing.
Yeah, until we learn how they fight, our\nonly real option is to fumble around until\nwe find something that works.
I was prepared for the way to be fraught\nwith difficulties, but this is taking far\nlonger than I imagined it would.
How long has it been since we entered\nthis tree, anyway?
Sunlight doesn't penetrate the canopy,\nwhich makes it difficult to tell—though I'd\nwager we're well past nightfall.
And it still feels like we're just climbing\nin place. Boo, man! Boo.
I understand your haste, but it's important\nfor us to pace ourselves.
There's no sense in facing Nedrick and\nJinlorda if we're all utterly exhausted.
Chelle's right. Better to stay on an even\nkeel than rush ahead.
I just hope there's somewhere nearby\nwhere we can rest and avoid the fiends.
Actually, it looks like there's a big hole\nin the tree just up there.
Let's check it out. If it looks safe enough,\nwe'll camp there for the night.
(Each time night falls lately, strange\nthoughts find their way into my mind.)
(Perhaps it's best to take a walk and\nclear my head.)
Hello, Gatov. Have you been awake\nall this time?
Hard for an old man to sleep soundly\nwhen his daughter's on watch.
Then Sheila is awake as well.
Not ever? How can she function?!
She is able to recover and heal without\nthe benefit of rest.
Hmm. I suppose that must be the case,\nconsidering she's made it this far.
...Just like you, I'm having trouble\nsleeping, so I'm going to go shake\nthe cobwebs out a little.
Don't go too far. The mana filling up this\nhollow is powerful. We'll be safe so long\nas we stay within it.
Of course. I'll be back shortly.
It feels as though the deeper I go,\nthe more powerful the mana becomes.
It's like I'm being wrapped up in it.\nIt's almost...calming.
Could it be because I am approaching\nthe center of the tree?
(Blast, but I keep thinking back to what\nTartarus said that day...)
You delude yourself. Perhaps this is\nborn of your despair at losing our king.
(When I first met the prince, I found His\nMajesty's likeness in him. I know this.)
(Yet it is also true that\n{player_name} does not have\nHis Majesty's blood in his veins.)
(Enough! I need not trouble myself with\nsuch things!)
(The prince has ever continued to work\ntoward a world of peace.)
(That proves above all else that he is the\ntrue inheritor of His Majesty's will!)
A king has no cause to surround himself\nwith an errant gaggle of lickspittles.\nA king is absolute, sui generis.
His Majesty was indeed a superhuman\nman possessed of overwhelming power.
A superhuman next to whom none could\nstand as an equal.
Even one of his actual bloodline would find\nit difficult to pull even with his strength.
And if it becomes clear that the prince is\nnot of His Majesty's bloodline, all manner\nof difficulties will arise...
How long will these thoughts haunt me?!
I've been waffling like this for so long,\nand all it's done is make trouble for my\nfriends on the battlefield.
I sense a remarkably strong mana coming\nfrom over there. Is it perhaps a mana fount\nor somesuch?
This area is so replete with mana it's\nturning into a palpable mist!
This place truly must be special for mana\nto take on physical form.
I...I can't see what's in front of me.\nI have to hurry back!
